sec.p:
Parties to a learning transaction are required to be able to support these six Open-edi characteristics as requirements governing the DMAs of the LET provider in their IT systems.
The six key characteristics by which Open-edi is recognized and defined are:
- actions based upon following rules;
- commitment of the parties involved;
- communications among parties automated;
- parties control and maintain their states;
- parties act autonomously; and,
- multiple simultaneous transactions can be supported.
See further Clause 5 “Characteristics of Open-edi” in ISO/IEC 15944-1..The ILCM principles reflect and support the six key characteristics of Open-edi.
